<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="8" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="9.[192,1440,635,691]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,364,635,659]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Life history.</emphasis>
This species is polyphagous with larval hosts recorded from nine families, especially 
<taxonomicName box="[192,307,667,691]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Fabaceae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Matthews and Lott 2005)" baseAuthorityName="Matthews and Lott" baseAuthorityYear="2005" box="[368,874,667,691]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cucurbitaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">
Cucurbitaceae (
<bibRefCitation author="Matthews, D. L. &amp; T. A. Lott" box="[560,866,667,691]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" pagination="1 - 324" refId="ref20718" refString="Matthews, D. L., and T. A. Lott 2005. Larval hostplants of the Pterophoridae (Lepidoptera: Pterophoroidea). Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute 76: 1 - 324. ISBN: 1 - 887988 - 20 - 3." type="journal article" year="2005">Matthews and Lott 2005</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="8" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="9.[192,1440,715,772]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,366,715,739]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Distribution.</emphasis>
Pantropical. In 
<collectingCountry box="[555,722,716,740]" name="Bahamas" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">The Bahamas</collectingCountry>
, known from New Providence Island and previously reported from North Andros (
<bibRefCitation author="Matthews, D. L. &amp; J. Y. Miller &amp; M. J. Simon &amp; G. Goss" box="[441,703,748,772]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" pagination="1 - 12" refId="ref20878" refString="Matthews, D. L., J. Y. Miller, M. J. Simon, and G. Goss. 2012. Observations of plume moths on North Andros Island, Bahamas, and notes on new records and species previously recorded from the Bahamas (Lepidoptera: Pterophoridae). Insecta Mundi 0236: 1 - 12." type="book chapter" year="2012">Matthews et al. 2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="8" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[192,1439,795,852]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,343,795,819]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Comments.</emphasis>
As noted by 
<bibRefCitation author="Matthews, D. L. &amp; J. Y. Miller &amp; M. J. Simon &amp; G. Goss" box="[493,761,796,820]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" pagination="1 - 12" refId="ref20878" refString="Matthews, D. L., J. Y. Miller, M. J. Simon, and G. Goss. 2012. Observations of plume moths on North Andros Island, Bahamas, and notes on new records and species previously recorded from the Bahamas (Lepidoptera: Pterophoridae). Insecta Mundi 0236: 1 - 12." type="book chapter" year="2012">Matthews et al. (2012)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[771,885,796,820]" name="Bahamas" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Bahamas</collectingCountry>
specimens thus far observed have a somewhat paler ground color and lack the bold ochraceous-tawny coloration of mainland specimens.
</paragraph>
